### Steps to reproduce

1. Create a `MaterialApp` with only a `onGenerateInitialRoutes` callback.
2. Implement `onGenerateInitialRoutes` to return the initial route based on the `String initialRoute` parameter. Include a fallback to the default route.
3. Run the app, either through a deeplink or just via the default launcher.

### Expected results

If a deeplink was opened with `/feature`, I would assume `onGenerateInitialRoutes` to get that exact value and be able to continue. If it is opened without a specific deeplink, I would assume `initialRoute` to be the default `/`.

The reason for this is to avoid the behavior of multiple routes being created via `onGenerateRoute` when a deeplink with a leading slash is provided:

1. onGenerateRoute called with `/`
2. onGenerateRoute called again with `/feature`

The docs of `WidgetsApp.initialRoute` state:

>   /// If the route name starts with a slash, then it is treated as a "deep link",
>   /// and before this route is pushed, the routes leading to this one are pushed
>   /// also. For example, if the route was `/a/b/c`, then the app would start
>   /// with the four routes `/`, `/a`, `/a/b`, and `/a/b/c` loaded, in that order.
>   /// Even if the route was just `/a`, the app would start with `/` and `/a`
>   /// loaded. You can use the [onGenerateInitialRoutes] property to override
>   /// this behavior.


### Actual results

No screen is shown if there is no `onGenerateRoute`, even if it would be empty.

Also, when adding `navigatorObservers`, you'll get the following assertion issue:

> ════════ Exception caught by widgets library ═══════════════════════════════════
> If no route is provided using home, routes, onGenerateRoute, or onUnknownRoute, a non-null callback for the builder property must be provided, and the other navigator-related properties, navigatorKey, initialRoute, and navigatorObservers, must have their initial values (null, null, and the empty list, respectively).
> 'package:flutter/src/widgets/app.dart':
> Failed assertion: line 393 pos 10: '(home != null || routes.isNotEmpty || onGenerateRoute != null || onUnknownRoute != null) ||
>              (builder != null &&
>                  navigatorKey == null &&
>                  initialRoute == null &&
>                  navigatorObservers.isEmpty)'

I wonder if it is simply missing a case for `onGenerateInitialRoutes != null` in the assertion. 🤔 

## Workaround

By adding an empty `onGenerateRoute` the screen is shown.

```dart
return MaterialApp(
  onGenerateRoute: (_) => null,
  onGenerateInitialRoutes: (initialRoute) {
     // ...
  },
);
```

In case of `navigatorObservers`, the assertion will also pass if we have add an empty `onGenerateRoute`:

```dart
return MaterialApp(
  onGenerateRoute: (_) => null,
  onGenerateInitialRoutes: (initialRoute) {
     // ...
  },
  navigatorObservers: [NavigatorObserver()],
);
```

